The effect of mental arithmetic is that (Fig. 1 B) there is a high peak 
of energy at 10 Hz which confirms that energy suppression has been 
influenced by mental arithmetic but not as intensely as by eye-opening. 
Mental arithmetic, in the other subject, caused almost complete suppres- 
sion of the energy peak at 8 Hz and a partial suppression of energy at 
about 12 Hz. Considerable differences in power spectral densities were 
found between individual subjects but individual patterns of distribution 
of energy were relatively constant over a period from six to ten minutes 
in duration (Fig. 1 B). 
