Calculation of the ratio of differences between power spectral den- 
sities during eye-opening or mental arithmetic with eyes closed and the 
power spectral density with eyes closed, as a percentage of the eyes 
closed density at each frequency level (Fig. 3) demonstrated a suppression 
of power at all frequencies (0--30 Hz by eye-opening and mental arith- 
metic. The suppression due to eye-opening was definitely greater at 
10 ttz and at higher frequencies. The second example confirms enhance- 
ment of power at low frequencies by nearly 100% by eye-opening and 
suppression by mental arithmetic. Suppression of power occurs at 20 Hz 
with eye-opening. 
Quantitative Changes 
The mean enhancements and suppressions of power have been cal- 
culated for eleven subjects in which data from the three eye-opening 
conditions and three calculation conditions have been pooled (Fig. 4). 
Enhancement of power in delta and low theta range (under 5.0 IIz) by 
eye-opening and suppresssion by mental arithmetic was found. Power at 
alpha frequencies around 10 Hz was suppressed during calculation but 
more intensely during eye-opening when characteristic suppression of 
