tion procedure for all classi ﬁcation methods (standard SVM,
TB-SVM, and ξ-SOCP in their linear and nonlinear versions)
and for all ﬁve datasets without performing feature selection.
The average performance among all techniques for each data
is also reported. The two best performances among all
