sures of the synchronization in the relevant connections indi-cate two types of di ﬀerent behaviors in regard to the cases of
correct responses and incorrect responses. In the ﬁrst case,
synchronization is consistently higher than in the case ofincorrect responses, indicating a di ﬀerent kind of resolution
strategy whose neurological correlate shows a coordinatedintegration of di ﬀerent brain areas.
