IV. S IMULATIONS
In this section, we present two results obtained using
the proposed methodology. The ﬁrst experiment is designed
to study the role of each cortex in cognitive tasks. Here,
we present the results for the classiﬁcation of EEG signals
recorded from different cortices into active and rest classes.
The second experiment classiﬁes the EEG signals based on
the difﬁculty level of the task. The EEG signals from both
active and rest states are classiﬁed and the signals from all
the channels are considered in this experiment. The results
obtained from both experiments are given below:
