Abstract — This assertion proposed a statistical modeling of 
recorded EEG signal where Gaussian distribution is utilized to 
classify the signals from a Mental Arithmetic Task for 
categorizing Bad counters and Good-counters (those who 
required excessive efforts for the task or not respectively) of 36 
subjects. Bad-counters finish the arithmetic task with a high 
level of difficulty and Good-counters finish the arithmetic task 
with no difficulty. The dataset of this paper carries EEG 
recordings of 36 subject’s performance of mental arithmetic 
tasks in the active and resting state. The dataset used here is 
taken from PhysioNet database platform where 22 channels 
are used. Here Discrete wavelet transform is used to divide the 
dataset signals into a number of sets. The main aspects of this 
paper are to set up a model which can analyze arithmetic Task 
signals to find Good or Bad it is. As a result of this work, after 
completing the classification of EEG data, proposed statistical 
modeling yielded a 72.22% accuracy. 
 
Keywords— Electroencephalogram (EEG), Discrete wavelet 
transform (DWT), Channel selection, Mental arithmetic task, 
Gaussian distribution. 
I. INTRODUCTION  
 
 Brain is an organ of electro-chemicals and an 
electroencephalogram (EEG) signal can be used for 
recording its electrical activity. The EEG signals are 
extremely erratic in character and it provides significant 
knowledge regarding the condition of the brain. They are 
non-Gaussian, non-linear and non-stationary by definition. 
EEG signals are used for many applications for example: 
diagnosis of seizure, epilepsy, sleep disorders and detection 
of tumors etc. It is also used for mental task classification 
[1]. 
 
 A standard EEG signal has 10-100v amplitude and 1-
100Hz frequency while measured from the scalp. Electrodes 
are inserted on the subject's scalp to determine the signals. 
The 10–20 electrode placement scheme developed for 
Electroencephalography specifies electrode positions. The 
relationship between the fundamental area of the cerebral 
cortex and the location of an electrode created the 10-20 
system of an EEG. The frontal, paternal, temporal, and 
occipital lobes are located in the cerebral cortex and these 
four cortices' electrical activity are captured by EEG signals, 
which aid in understanding their function [2]. 
 
 EEG recording used in a wide range of applications, 
starting from basic research on brain organization, 
development, and cognition to clinical research and claims 
for managing patient illness conditions. Some applications 
are Brain Computer Interface, Epilepsy monitoring, Sleep 
studies, Produce biofeedback, drug and surgical treatments. 
We worked on the Brain Computer Interface in this   
assertion, which is a route for communicating directly 
between the human nervous system and output devices. 
 
Fourier Transform (FT), Fast Fourier Transform (FFT), 
Short Time Fourier Transform (STFT) and Wavelet 
Transform (WT) are the mathematical tools which are 
introduced for EEG signal feature extraction. Wavelet 
transform (WT) offers a broad range of applications in the 
area of Digital Signal Processing. Wavelet transforms are 
classified as continuous, discrete. And it’s a combined use 
of the process of convolution, which involves reversing, 
shifting, multiplying, and integrating them [3]. 
 
Since the EEGs discovery, people have postulated that it 
may be used for communication and control, allowing the 
brain to perform on the situation without the usual 
middlemen of peripheral nerves and muscles. Brain 
computer interface’s purpose is to create a new type of 
communication system that allows the human brain to 
control equipment and devices without the usage of muscle 
movements. BCI uses machine learning to transform EEG 
signals by brain activity into control directives. BCI is a 
biological communication system that connects the exterior 
world within real time also in a natural way. By converting 
brain signals into control commands BCI accelerates the 
communication between the brain and external world 
devices. Those who are suffering a neuromuscular disease, 
BCI can be highly benefited by using their brain signal to 
access multiple tasks. BCI working principle consists of five 
steps- first step is measurement brain activity, second is 
signal preprocessing, third step is extraction of features, 
fourth step is classification, fifth step is control interface 
which converts the classified signals to readable data for 
devices such as computers. Those phases are a very 
important part that highly influence the accuracy of the 
proposed BCI model. 
 
Mental cognitive workload refers to the mental effort 
level required to complete different tasks such as mental 
arithmetic problem solving, reading or writing and they can 
be evaluated by tracking changes in neurophysiological 
parameters like EEGs. It indicated the amount of mental 
effort exerted by a task on an individual. Identification of 
mental workload during cognitive tasks is an important area 
in cognitive neuroscience and other real-world applications. 
Cognitive workload measurement is an essential problem in 
numerous study and application regions of human computer 
interaction because it may be used to assess the potency of 
interfaces and create adjustable interaction techniques. The 
advancement of real-time measure of the mental workload 
may lead to the formation of intelligent systems which 
can adapt instruction and maintain subjects in an ideal 
