 CO
NCLUSION  
 
This study presents the classifications of EEG signals under 
mental cognitive stress as a Brain Computer Interface work. 
The dataset was gathered from 36 healthy individuals of 
similar ages. Here we present a novel methodology to make 
statistical modelling. We have extracted features using the 
Support Vector Machine classifier from the given EEG 
signals of two different groups. Classification results 
showed that selecting features from all channels and models 
from all channels resulted in an average accuracy of 
72.22%. Accuracy level using this dataset and proposed 
method satisfy us. Our statistical model-based algorithms 
had the best accuracy compared to other classification 
algorithms. This gives researchers a chance to dig deeper 
into the classification of mental cognitive stress. Many more 
advanced feature selection and classification methods could 
be used to further improve the classification of mental 
arithmetic task performance. 
