ently on easy, medium and difficult problem types, presumably
because they underperformed across problem types in general
(Ps>0.12). All other groups showed the expected patterns, i.e.
performing better on easy compared with moderate and diffi-
cult problems, and moderate compared with difficult problems
(Ps<0.04).
