in synchrony. Therefore, it is likely that delta phase synchrony
reported in near EEG electrode pairs, like Pz—P2 and P2—PPO1,
are contaminated by volume conduction.However,we also founddelta phase synchrony between distant electrode pairs including
frontal, central and parietal locations, like F3—P1, F3—Pz andF3—PPO1, suggesting expertise-related differences in functional
connectivity between distant brain regions. Volume conduction
is a severe issue over near but not over distant electrodes. Sec-ond, our results could be explained by fundamentally differ-
ent brain functions between experts and novices assuming thatDownloaded from https://academic.oup.com/cercor/article/34/2/bhae025/7607164 by guest on 14 May 2025
