experts followed the math demonstrations,but novices were just
thinking other task-irrelevant thoughts. Indeed, novices reported
being less engaged and having a poorer understanding of the
demonstrations than experts. However, we can assume that alsonovices did their best to understand the demonstrations because
all the participants knew they would be asked to explain the
demonstrationslatertotheexperimenter.Third,despiteweaimedfor age-matched groups, due to technical problems and rejec-
tion of several participants, the age of the expert and novice
