First of all, we find from the reports that through different classification methods,
using various signal analysis characteristics, a particular group of signals was identified
as the most relevant for the detection and characterization of the mental arithmetic task.
This group of signals is captured from several areas of the head (prefrontal, frontal, central,
parietal, temporal, occipital). This fact is in agreement with the mapping of brain areas
presented in Section 3.2, with reference to the neurodynamics of the brain. Sensors 2024 ,24, 3316 23 of 27
