 Abstract  – Solving mathematical tasks or puzz les is one of 
the most common learning processes in many learning 
activities. This task can be either simple or complex depending 
on the level of study. Many individuals feel the fear of math 
tasks which will hamper the learning process due to stress. 
Henc e, recognition of stress plays a crucial  role in many 
learning activities. In this  work , machine learning -based 
automatic recognition of mental stress during math puzzle 
solving is developed using EEG signals. EEG signals a re 
recorded  using Enobio 8 device  in two categories, one during 
math puzzle solving and another in happy state with audio -
visual stimuli with funny video clips . The raw signals are 
preprocessed to remove the artifacts using 2 -40Hz band pass 
filter. Filtered data is used to extract EEG ban ds. EEG relative 
band power is analyzed to observe the changes during math task 
and relaxation. The two mental states are classified using Long 
Short Term Memory (LSTM) deep learning model. The  
classification accuracy of 86 % is achieved in beta band.  
 
Inde x Terms – Electroencephalogra m, Brain Computer Interface , 
Deep  learning, Mental Arithmetic , Long Short Term Memory, 
Stress.  
 
I.  INTRODUCTION  
 In the fast -paced and demanding world of today, 
individuals often find themselves grappling with various forms 
of stress. One particularly intriguing facet of this phenomenon 
is cognitive stress, which emerges during complex tasks such 
as mathematical problem -solving. The human brain's response 
to stress during mathematical activities is a subject of growing 
interest , as it not only affects cognitive performance but also 
sheds light on the intricate interplay between the mind and 
mathematics  [1]. Furthermore, the search for effective relaxation 
techniques has led to the exploration of innovative 
approaches, including audio -visual stimuli. These stimuli are 
believed to induce relaxation and have the potential to 
modulate brain activity as evidenced by quantitative EEG 
(Electroencephalogram) changes. This confluence of cognitive 
stress recognition during mathematical tas ks and the influence 
of audio -visual stimuli on brain activity represents a fascinating intersection in the fields of psychology, 
neuroscience, and education  [2].  
Mathematics is a discipline that frequently elicits stress 
and anxiety in individuals of all  ages. This phenomenon, often 
referred to as math anxiety, can have a significant impact on 
mathematical performance and learning outcomes. 
Understanding cognitive stress during mathematical tasks is 
vital for several reasons  such as academic performance, 
psychological well -being and neurological implications.  In 
recent years, there has been growing interest in leveraging 
technology to promote relaxation and stress reduction. One 
promising avenue is the use of audio -visual stimuli, which 
combine auditory an d visual elements to induce relaxation. 
This research area is signi ficant for stress management, 
neurofeedback etc . By understanding the neural correlates of 
stress during math -related activities and how audio -visual 
interventions can modulate brain activi ty, researchers can 
develop more efficient  educational strategies, stress 
management tools, and therapies for individuals facing math -
related stress and other forms of psychological distress. This 
research has the potential to improve learning outcomes, 
mental health, and overall quality of life for a broad range of 
individuals  [1-2]. 
This exploration holds promise for understanding how 
people can use the power of technology to manage stress and 
optimize cognitive performance in educational and real -world 
environment. This research study will investigate  the key 
aspects of cognitive stress recognition during mathematical 
tasks  and the intriguing  EEG changes that follow audio -visual 
stimuli for relaxation, by considering  their potential 
implications for enhan cing mental well -being and learning 
outcomes . Deep Learning based LSTM model is used to 
classify stress and relaxed states.  
  
II. BACKGROUND  
This section analyzes and summarizes some of the deep 
learning methods  used in stress recognition  and mental 
arithm etic task classification .  
Lokesh M et al., [3] have proposed a hybrid method using 
