 This work explores how our brains react when we're 
stressed whi le doing math and how we can use relaxing 
videos and technology to help . In today's busy world, 
understanding how stress affects us during math is crucial . 
This study reveals an increase in alpha relative band power 
during the 'happy' state, indicating rel axation. The 
classification of 'happy' and 'stressed' states using LSTM 
achieved an accuracy of 86% in the beta band. Furthermore, 
there is potential to enhance this system for improved 
accuracy and its application to other mathematical tasks.   
