smoothing, the alpha frequency peaks (8 -13 Hz) are still clear, along with some ac tivity at lower 
frequencies, possibly theta (4 -8 Hz) or delta (0.5 -4 Hz) waves.  
During the computational task, we see a clear decrease in alpha waves and an increase in 
activity at higher frequencies, especially in the beta range (13 -30 Hz), indicating inc reased 
cognitive activity and concentration.  After smoothing, higher frequency activities are still evident, 
especially beta waves and possibly some gamma waves (>30 Hz).  
