Standard deviation measures the variability of brain activity, helping to identify stability or 
change in the EEG signal. A high standard deviation may  indicate instability or rapid shifts in 
cognitive states, which is particularly important when analyzing different stages of arithmetic 
tasks. This feature enhances the accuracy of classifying cognitive load levels in the study . 
Standard deviation is comm only used in EEG research to assess signal variability under 
different experimental conditions. Menon et al. (2000) showed that increased standard deviation 
corresponds to more complex task phases, reflecting significa nt changes in brain activity [3 ]. 
Soleymani et al. (2012) also noted that standard deviation is a key metric in distinguishing 
cognitive and emotional states, especially during tasks requiring high cognitive eff ort [5]. 
