By contrast, the ‘‘optimum’’ channels related to task
complexity and short-term learning of the control subjects
are mainly distributed in the left-lateral frontal and bilateralparietooccipital brain regions (Fig. 5f–h, classiﬁcation ac-
curacy: 0.6603, 0.6938, and 0.7059), which are consistent
