representation is a grouping list (which denotes a speciﬁc cluster-
ing of electrodes), and the Variational Information metric (VI) is the
appropriate dissimilarity measure. The former reﬂects a speciﬁc
realisation of the brain’s functional segregation, while the latter
facilitates the pairwise comparison of distinct segregations. If we
neatly denote, the brain-state representation (derived via the
