et al. 2022 ).ML algorithm: Independent-Component-Analysis 
(ICA) is performed for removal of artifacts during the 
data pre-processing stage. EEG is a random signal 
and only specific segments contribute for the attain -
ment of objective. The ICA dimensionality reduction 
helps to find relevant linear and nonlinear dependen -
cies both EEG and noise parameters in the signal. 
The matrix multiplication of signals enables non- 
Gaussian distribution which aids in generating inde -
pendent EEG signals that are noise free. The arith -
metic objective was to subtract two numbers serially 
(Looi et al. 2016 ). All tests began with the verbalized 
communication of four-digit number subtracted from 
two-digit numbers. Each recording contains 180s of 
artifact-free resting state EEG and cognition numer -
ation EEG segments for 60s. A total of 36 healthy 
volunteers’ EEG recordings were acquired in two sep-
arate sets in the resting and active states.
A total of 66 individuals were initially signed up. 
Thirty patients were not included in the study 
because of the poor EEG quality.
Table 1represents the subject information with 
age, gender, count quality, and the number of sub-
tractions. This table gives an insight regarding effi-
cient understanding of task done by the participants 
selected. The split of data acquired to various classes 
can be handled using this demarcation. The conclud -
ing sample size was 36. Participants were considered 
eligible if regular or rectified visual acuity, normal 
color perception were found, and no medical signs 
and symptoms of higher-level cognitive dysfunction, 
and no linguistic or gestural learning disabilities were 
reported. Psychotropic medication use, alcohol or 
