SVM algorithm has proven to be an effective method 
for resolving practical binary classification problems 
(Fatimah et al. 2020 ). SVM has been proved to outper -
form other supervised learning approaches. SVM is a 
robust classifier which is capable of performing classifica -
tion using generated support vectors (SV). The SV cre-
ates a linearly separable hyperplane using kernel trick 
methodology. The decision boundary is generated using 
the various mathematical formulations pertaining to the 
linear, polynomial and Gaussian models. SVM have been 
one of the most widely used classification methods in 
recent years, owing to its solid theoretical basis and high 
generalization capacity. The SVM method is used to find 
