The classification is done using SVM binary algo-
rithm. This requires two variables which are separated 
as class 0 and class 1. The features are F4 and F8, 
which have been further reduced in accordance with 
the facts from the literature. The F4 and F8 features 
are used for classification with various kernels namely 
linear, radial, sigmoid, and polynomial which are 
shown in Figures 23–26 . The use of kernels can 
accommodate more SV into certain classes. The linear 
kernel provided distinctive classification across the 
hyperplane. The projections in different dimensions 
give other kernels. The radial kernel has larger accur -
acy which implies more demarcation of feature 
vectors.
SVM is a data classification algorithm that offers 
an accuracy (Gogna et al. 2023 ) of 86.1%, due to its 
