SVM classifiers perform better than the Naive 
Bayes approach in terms of prediction accuracy and 
speed. A work carried out for concentration (Bird 
et al. 2018 ) aided EEG classification produced an 
accuracy of 56.3% for correlation-based dataset using 
Naïve Bayes classifier. Since a sample of training 
instances is used, the decision stage requires less 
memory. SVM performs well because it has a vast 
dimensional space and a distinct separation margin. 
ML trade-offs can be seen in SVM and kNN. kNN 
classifier for mental workload using 5-fold classes 
(Cheema et al. 2018 ) produces an accuracy of 61.43% 
of accuracy. This model also incorporates optimiza -
tion of features selected using statistical parameters. 
SVM can only recognize a small subset of patterns, 
but it is simpler to grasp and requires significantly 
less compute than kNN. On the other hand, even 
while kNN may find incredibly complicated patterns, 
its output is more challenging to understand.
4. Conclusions
The EEG data helps us fetching insights regarding the 
thinking ability of an individual. This motto is 
achieved using Electroencephalogram visual imagery 
data in the work proposed in this article. The learning 
algorithm used to check this capability utilizes a min-
imum feature for immediate interpretation. The use 
cases of the algorithm are for a wider horizon. The 
number of channels for executing mental arithmetic 
task categorization for best accuracy was implemented 
using a linear classifier. The moderation in the ker-
nels used also intended to improvise the performance. The methodology emphasizes that the performance of 
mental arithmetic exercises greatly relies on the 
frontal lobe excitatory activity rather than the other 
data collection points. The model described despite of 
the lower computational complexity is not utilized for 
real time datasets which helps understanding the non-
linear complexities exhibited by the EEG signal. In 
the future works module for IoMT(Internet of 
Medical Things)-based EEG acquisition and validation 
can be implemented. People who have lost their abil-
ity to process cognitive activity will benefit signifi -
cantly from this algorithm which is used to validate 
tasks with minimal features. The BCI allows the users 
to communicate and control external devices 
(Beniczky et al. 2021 ) can also be designed using this 
simple more efficient model. Using an assorted signal 
would allow the user to interact with the system bet-
ter. IQ levels, concentration analysis (activity in the 
prefrontal cortex) can be diagnosed using trained 
models of EEG (Yadava et al. 2017 ). The ML classifi -
cation models can be exploited in studying the activ -
ity of patients with autism and plays a major role in 
neuro-marketing (Goldberger et al. 2000 ).
