  After normalization of  the entire frequency band for every 
scalp locations , t-test value was conducted to calculate  for the 
correct and incorrect answer s to indicate the significant difference  
between the findings with control . The values of th e significant 
difference were set at  P < 0.05.     
 
 
3.0  RESULTS AND DISCUSSION  
 
For th e mental arithmetic task (MA07), there were thirteen 
participants involved with five trials for each person. Generally, out 
of 65 trials (13 participants × 5 trials), 37 correct answers were 
given by the participan ts while another 28 answer s were incorrect.  
 
3.1 Functional Connectivity  
 
Example of signal pathways of the cortical networks for 
information sources and information sinks during the mental task 
which can be observed is shown in Figure 4. The results were 
obtained using PDC which delineate the  information so urces and 
sinks according to brain regions.  Information source is where 
information was generated when participant started to calculate 
while information sink is where information was  sent to other brain 
area for various executive function skills to obtain the answer to the 
arithmetic task given.  
 
