commonly frontal area (i.e.: 𝐹𝑝1, 𝐹𝑝2, 𝐹3, 𝐹4, 𝐹7, 𝐹8, and 𝐹𝑧) and 
temporal area (i.e.:  𝑇3, 𝑇4, 𝑇5, and  𝑇6) were involved in the mental 
subtraction task. Few information sources were produce d in 
parietal area (i.e.:  𝑃3 and 𝑃4) during mental task. From the figure , 
scalp locations 𝐹𝑝1, 𝐹8, and  𝑇4 were  frequently use d by participants 
in giving correct answers whil e scalp locations  𝐹𝑝1 and 𝐹𝑝2 were 
frequently used for the incorrect answers.  
