Finally, while anxiety is generally expected to have a negative effect on performance, this study showed that a certain amount of 
anxiety not only plays an inhibitory role but also enhances attention during tasks. Identifying the relationship between math anxiety 
and mathematics teachers seems of crucial importance as well (Atabek et al., 2022 ) so that if there is any meaningful relationship, all 
teachers who teach math can be informed about this anxiety to reduce test anxiety in college and school students. All the studies 
conducted in this field are to understand the relationship between anxiety and thinking skills. Apart from importance in academic 
