Mental arithmetic canbehelpful fortheevaluation ofneurodevelopmental disorders arising from atypical
development ofthebrain. Wepropose anovel explainable machine learning method forclassifying mental
arithmetic calculation tasks from resting brain states andgood from badcalculations using Electroencephalog-
raphy. Empirical mode decomposition features areextracted from intrinsic mode functions oftheaverage signals
ofalltrials. Most relevant features tothemental arithmetic tasks areranked byarandom forest-based recursive
feature elimination method. These features identify thechanges infrequency bands ofthebrain rhythms, such as
delta, theta, andalpha, during mental tasks forthefirsttime inliterature. These unique explainable features are
alsoused toidentify brain areas such asfrontal, temporal, andoccipital lobes involved inmental arithmetic tasks.
Moreover, ourapproach describes thememory regions andthatbadcalculations excite thebrain areas, mostly
related toemotions such asfrustration andanxiety duetostressful mental arithmetic. Using arandom forest
classifier, beating thestate-of-the-art, thismethod achieved classification accuracies of99.30 %and98.33 %for
resting vscalculation andgood vsbadcalculation brain tasks, respectively. Also, ourmethod outperformed the
state ofartinhandling theinter-subject variability andachieved 98.17±0.47 %and97.19±0.95 %classifi-
cation accuracies forresting vscalculation andgood vsbadcalculation tasks, respectively.
1.Introduction
Electroencephalography (EEG) electrical brain activity isthemost
effective physiological measure forassessing cognitive states duetoits
ability toshow theelectrical behavior ofthecortex. Multichannel EEG
hasbeen used invarious cognitive studies toclassify mental tasks,
including emotion recognition, classification ofsleep phases, sleep pa-
thology detection, driver sleepiness recognition, epilepsy analysis, and
mental arithmetic [1].Investigations have shown thatmental arithmetic
evaluations built onEEG signals canhelp detect math anxiety that
causes stress [2],andsyndromes such asattention deficit hyperactivity
disorder (ADHD) [3,4] andautism spectrum disorder (ASD) [5].Various
factors areinvolved inthedevelopment ofmathematical skills from
childhood such asheritage language [6],numerical knowledge and
spatial reasoning [7],cognitive andnumber abilities forearly arithmetic
learning [8],andworking memory [9].Besides, mental arithmetic forall
agesinvolves information processing, emotions, andmath anxiety [10].These functions areperformed bydifferent brain areas, including the
frontal, prefrontal, cerebellum, temporal, parietal, andoccipital lobes,
during mental arithmetic [11].Activity inthese brain areas canbe
assessed bydifferent frequency bands, such asdelta, theta, alpha, and
gamma [12].Asmental arithmetic tasks involve different brain regions
andwaves, acomprehensive analysis ofhow thisactivity hasbeen
performed isrequired.
Various studies have been conducted toanalyze mental arithmetic
tasks from EEGusing machine learning onpublicly available datasets in
different ways. Such asthemental arithmetic tasklevels classification
[13],difficulty levels andn-back tasks inmental arithmetic calculations
[14],real-time mental taskcategorization [15],identification ofstress
andnon-stress categories [16],frequency spectrum analysis during a
written mathematical task[17],andquantification ofcortical engage-
ment during mental arithmetic tasks [18].Machine learning classifica-
tionpipeline modules include handcrafted feature extraction, selection,
andclassification. Feature extraction isthemost significant part of
