above forfeature extraction ofresting vscalculation isused forthegood
vsbadcalculation state.2.2.2. Feature selection
This section introduces theRF-RFE feature selection method for
removing redundant features from theEMD feature set.Therandom
forest (RF) algorithm isanensemble learning method using decision
trees asconstituent learners. RFiseasy toimplement andhasgood
precision androbustness andinterpretability [44].Itiswell-known that
shallow trees have alarge bias, anddeep trees have alarge variance. RF
constructs abagging ensemble using bootstrap sampling, andeach
sample setisused totrain adeep (low-bias, high-variance) decision tree.
Intraining thedecision trees, arandom subset ofthefeatures isused to
grow thetree ateach node. This process, combined with bootstrap
sampling, generates decision trees whose predictions areindependent.
Thefinal prediction isthen obtained bycombining thedecisions ofin-
dividual trees (amajority voteistaken inthecaseofclassification). This
reduces thevariance ofthecombined decision, thusresulting inalow-
bias andlow-variance classifier. Due tothese characteristics, RFhas
become oneofthemost popular machine-learning algorithms.
