Intheproposed work, explainable features areobtained after
applying theRF-RFE feature selection method, which helped attain the
highest classification accuracy forboth resting vscalculation andgood
vsbad. Besides RF-RFE, wealsoused other feature selection methods,
such asF-score [14,19] ,binary Harris hawks optimization (BHHO) [26],
T-test [15,24] ,BAO [32],iterative neighborhood component analysis
(INCA) [13],andKruskal-Wallis test(KWT) [28],andtheobtained ac-
curacy isdemonstrated inFig.8.These methods areused byexisting
studies with traditional machine learning based onhandcrafted features.Itcanbeobserved inFig.8(a)thatforresting vscalculation classes,
NLSVM andRFhave obtained thehighest testclassification accuracy
using RF-RFE, whereas, forother feature selection methods, itremained
between 90%and96%,with INCA performing best inthese other
feature selection methods. INCA isaniterative process thatuses map-
ping functions such asnearest neighbor fortraining, andconvergence is
based onempirical observations [70].Though kNN performance
remained below 80%,itisthehighest compared toLDA andLSVM
linear classifiers because they donotperform well forournonlinear
feature set.Forgood vsbadcalculation classes, theperformance ofthe
proposed feature selection method RF-RFE showed thesame pattern as
resting vscalculation classes andobtained thehighest testaccuracy
compared totheother methods. RF-RFE isaniterative process that
eliminates alltheleast important features based ontheclassification
performance ofRF,asupervised method within thefeature selection
process [71].Whereas inother methods, features areanalyzed indi-
vidually. Besides, EMD features obtained from theIMFs captured the
EEG frequency bands, revealing subtle patterns responsible forthe
mental tasks performed bythesubjects.
Our findings highlight that thisresearch could help setanew
dimension fordeveloping EEG-based BCIapplications, specifically in
analyzing themathematical skills ofchildren who face heritage lan-
guage andlearning disabilities anddeveloping diagnostic systems for
ADHD andautism patients. This dataset isacquired from healthy sub-
jects inaspecific agerange; inthefuture, theproposed method willbe
