Further support for our interpretation of the trend described above can be 
derived from the calculation of entropy reduction without the self-transition of the 
microstates. If we exclude the self-transition, the entropy reduction is reduced to 
concatenation of different microstates. In this case the gifted subjects (Hred = 0.61, 
SD = 0.09) exhibit a significantly higher entropy reduction than the normal (Hred = 
0.48, SD = 0.06) subjects (Z = -3.31, P < 0.01). The sequence of microstates may 
be considered as a Markovian chain. The concatenation of microstates without 
