i=1(vi(t)−v(t))2 (1)Identifying Gifted Thinking Activities 125
 where v(t)=( v1(t),… ,vn(t)), which is the vector of potentials of signals at time t. Here,
n is the number of EEG electrodes, and v(t)=1
