then averaging (Fig. 1(B), Step
➂). Actual obtained
values within each frequency band were then com-pared with the upper and lower extremes of thesurrogate distribution (2.5% and 97.5% percentilefor a two-tailed test where α=0.05). If original
mean ERSP values fell outside of this envelope, theywere considered reliably d iﬀerent from the baseline;otherwise, they were considered nonsigniﬁcant and
