Cz, C4 and occipital recording sites. Notably, overother channels — particularly those characterizedby event-related synchronization (ERS) in the thetarange — a pattern of progressively increasing alphaand beta suppression can be discerned, with maximaldesynchronization in the ﬁnal 3s of the problem solv-ing phase. Finally, prominent theta ERS occurs overthe frontal midline around two and a half seconds
