continuous processing of premise information,
information maintenance and memory retention in theworking memory system, and response comparisonbetween the displayed conclusion and the inference
drawn from premises ( Knauﬀ et al., 2002; Fangmeier
et al., 2006 ). It depends on individual reasoning ability
and eﬀortful cognitive processing through interconnected
frontal and parietal cortical circuitry ( Blair, 2007 ).
The time–frequency analyses discover that, theta-
band neural activity is signiﬁcantly involved in the
deductive reasoning process, through the staged
spectral response and the emergence of long-distancephase coherence. As an important building-block of
functional signaling, theta oscillation is highly involved incognitive load and memory performances ( Klimesch,
1999; Sauseng et al., 2005 ). Thus, the signiﬁcant theta
response recorded in this experiment can be associated
with mental reasoning-induced workload required in diﬀer-
ent stages of the task. Moreover, the theta fronto-parietalcoherence can be viewed as a reﬂection of central exec-
utive functions of working memory load and mirrors the
activation of the fronto-parietal network ( Sauseng et al.,
2005 ). For the math-gifted adolescents, while responding
to more intensive fm theta response regarding higher
mental eﬀort of workload manipulations ( Itthipuripat
et al., 2013 ), the enhanced theta long-range coherence
in the fronto-parietal network reﬂects their more expanded
memory capacity in encoding and maintaining informationvia the highly integrated fronto-parietal cortical circuitry inthe reasoning process.
Functional network reorganization and workspace
pattern of network conﬁguration . By means of increased
long-range synchronizations, the math-gifted
adolescents exhibit greater shift of topological
organization to ‘‘workspace’’ conﬁguration than thecontrol subjects, which is manifested as more signiﬁcant
changes of network measures toward a shorter global
path, higher global eﬃciency, less modularity, less localclustering, and better-interconnected fronto-parietalnetwork architecture. This tendency of network
reorganization and the enhanced topological workspace
conﬁguration in the math-gifted brain can better facilitatetask-related functional interaction among discrete brain
regions and promote the level of global synchronizationTable 3. Local conﬁguration parameters of reasoning-related theta
