each task from the macro viewpoint of brain functions
for the computation processing. However, such EEGtopographies have limitation in spatial resolution, andneed to combine with fMRI data analysis for identifyingthe activated areas more accurately.
4.4. fMRI data analysis
fMRI makes the observation of the brain more accurate
and detailed by providing images of functional brain acti-vations to observe dynamic activation patterns within dif-
ferent areas of the brain for a given task ( Rosen,
Buckner, & Dale, 1998; Shulman & Rothman, 1998 ). It is
excellent in the space resolution, but inferior in the timeresolution.
