In above formulas,   TP (True Positive ) and T N (True 
Negative ) correctly predicted  positive  and negative 
outcome s. FP  (False Positive ) and FN  (False Negative ) 
incorrectly predicted positive  and negative outcome s.  The 
proportion of agreement that would result from raters 
classifying at random is known as Expected agreement (Pe).  
A. Training Process  
For CNN -LSTM model training, validation, and testing, 
the database was split into 80%, 10%, and 10% respectively. 
A mini -batch size of 64 is utilized for the training dataset. The 
The cost function is optimized by u tilizing  the Adam 
optimizer.  The training performance of a model over five 
epochs. Random shuffling was used after each epoch to 
reduce bias during training and iteration and help in faster 
training convergence The training was completed efficiently 
in 58 seconds ,with a total of 275  iterations (55 per epoch). 
The model effectively converged with a piecewise learning 
rate, achieving low loss and high acc.  
