Abstract —Stress is the non-specific response of human brain 
which changes according to the demand of day to day life. In this 
paper stress and relaxation of brain is identified from the 
activation of alpha ( α) and beta ( β) EEG bands depending on 
their power spectral density (PSD). Stress occurs due to 
sustained mental task in a test (Bengali, English, Math) environment and the work has been performed in to Reading, 
Writing and Mathematical problem-solving stages. When  ⁄ࢻࢼ    
power ratio is 1.5 or more it indicates stress. The relaxation of the brain is estimated taking the PSD at different time interval 
after the brain activity and when the ⁄ࢻࢼ ratio returns to the 
value of relax state then it is determined that relaxation is obtained. Finally brain relaxation is modeled with mathematical 
formulation based on ⁄ࢻࢼ power ratio.  
Keywords—EEG bands, stress, mental task, band power ratio, 
relaxation modeling
 
I. INTRODUCTION  
The higher level of cognitive engagement in any cognitive 
process indicates mental workload which has a direct impact 
on the quality of learning process for the learners [1]. An optimal level of mental workload facilitates an efficient learning process whereas cognitive overload negatively affects the task performance and causes a change in human behavior and directs towards stress [2]. Real-time measurement of mental stress can assist to identify the optimal level of mental workload and it enhances the subjective performance on the learning or test environment [3]. 
Stress can be estimated from perceptual, behavioral and 
physical responses to sustained mental activities. Evaluation of these responses to stress involves subjective estimations and perceptions at different test environment. Self-report questionnaires are one of the most commonly used methods to measure ones’ level of stress [4]. Evaluating the mental 
stress using questionnaires is a subjective method [5] and 
stress can be quantified from human bio-signals [6]. The stress can be evaluated from physical response from the changes of heart rate, respiratory rate, skin conductance, blood volume or temperature. EEG signal are subdivided in to several frequency bands with spectral analysis which are alpha bands (8-13 Hz), beta bands (14-30 Hz), delta (0.5-4 Hz) and theta (4-8 Hz) bands. In the EEG, increased EEG alpha wave activity has been associated with an increased level of relaxation, otherwise it decreases during stress condition [7]. Delta and theta band are activated during deep sleep or unconscious and for consciousness or mental stress the alpha and beta band activity are more. So, in this paper, 
beta and alpha activation is analyzed using PSD and ߙ/ߚ 
band power ratio is used as relaxation factor.  Many researchers are working on stress indication. To 
evoke cognitive loading mental arithmetic, decision making, 
memory retention, high workload, and multiple tasks 
solutions are taken previously as experiment. Most common experiments are Color-Stroop Task [8], Montreal Imaging Stress Task and basic arithmetic questions under time limits [9]. So WKY et.al developed a bio-marker in which mental workload based on the frontal activities were measured by a mobile single channel EEG system [3]. Authors in [10] demonstrated that alpha and theta activities have close relationship with cognitive performance and mental effort. Raghayachan et al.  showed that event-related Theta activity 
increases with memory load and it decreases steeply after 
completion of the task [11]. However, these findings were obtained from conventional multi-channel EEG with wet electrodes. Authors in [12] showed the activity of EEG bands during different emotional condition and mathematical modeling of these states. But there is found little work on brain relaxation analysis and modeling. 
In this work, subject’s mental stress is evaluated from 
EEG signals in a test environment during sustained mental activities. Cognitive workload is responsible for the stress which is identified from the non-stationary EEG signals. Mental workload changes human mental responses so relaxation analysis is also performed depending on their beta to alpha band power ratio. The more alpha band activity indicates relaxation of the brain whereas beta activity inverses this. A mathematical model is necessary to unify the brain relaxation analysis in different Bengali, English and Math test environments. So, in this paper a mathematical model is developed for brain relaxation which is the new outcome than the previous one. Fig.1 shows the flow chart of the proposed approach. 
The rest of this paper is organized as follows. Section II 
briefly introduces methodology of this proposed work. Experimental results and discussion justifying the PSD analysis for stress indication and mathematical modeling of brain relaxation are reported in Section IV. Finally, Section V concludes the result.
 
II. METHODOLOGY  
A.  Categorization of Mental Tasks 
This work focus on the identification of stress due to 
sustained mental task in the test environment. So Bengali, 
English and Mathematics tests are considered as the mental task stimuli to determine the stress of the learners. These  
