B. Subject Preparation
 
To select subjects, we have used random pick method. We 
have selected 52 subjects all aged from 20 to 23 (on average 
22.3). All were university students. The very common thing for all the subjects is that Bengali is the native language whereas English is the second one. It is noteworthy that the medium of instruction is English for entire course curriculum 
in the universities. It is also notable that selected subjects do 
not suffer from sleep disorder or any other severe diseases. The subjects were observed around 7 weeks in the sealed laboratory room and around 18 hours of data are recorded on an average. Moreover, the subjects were not aware of the study objectives. 
C. EEG Signal Acquisition 
EEG signals are collected in BME Lab, KUET using 
BIOPAC MP36 system. BIOPAC electrode lead set (SS2L), 
disposable vinyl electrodes (EL503), data collection unit (MP36 and MP150) with cable and power are required for acquisition the signal. The pictorial view of the EEG acquisition in the BME laboratory is shown in Fig. 2. The data acquisition protocol and the raw EEG signal with different EEG bands are shown in Figs. 3 and 4 respectively. One of the mentioning advantages of BIOPAC system is that it consists filtering to remove the power line carriers and divide the raw EEG signals in to different frequency bands (alpha, beta, delta and theta). For data collection process, at first in relaxed state 15 minute of data is recorded for further comparison. Then a mental task of 1-hour duration has been provided for observation. After 1 hour, immediately EEG data has been recorded. After 15 min. rest   
