III. RESULTS AND DISCUSSION  
A. Stress detection from PSD 
PSD analysis shows the activation of EEG bands due to 
different test environments. Table II shows the PSD based 
band activation. The delta and theta band are activated for deep sleep or unconsciousness stage of the brain. So, in this analysis alpha and beta activation is analyzed. Firstly, when the subjects were kept in relaxe d state the alpha activation is 
66% and ⁄ߙߚ band power ratio is 0.509.   
For Bengali, English and mathematical task the beta 
activity was greater than the alpha and the 	⁄ߙߚratio is 
approximately on average 1.5. The larger beta activity shows 
the stress condition of the brain. Fig. 5  shows the percentage 
of alpha and beta activity for relax stage and also for Bengali, English and Mathematics test environment. 
B. Brain relaxation Analysis with PSD 
Brain relaxation is analyzed with 	⁄ߙߚband power ratio. 
Table III shows that the 	⁄ߙߚband power ratio is decreasing 
over time which indicates that the beta activity is reducing 
whereas the alpha activity of brain is increasing so relaxation 
is obtained when the beta to alpha band power ratio returns to the value of the relax state. In this analysis 	⁄ߙߚRatio is taken 
as the relaxation factor. At the stage of relax the 	⁄ߙߚ Ratio 
is 0.509. The ratio is approximately 1.5 when the signal was 
taken is immediately after task. From the Table III, it is determined that after 2.5-hour brain is returning to the original relax state. 
In the case of brain relaxation English seems more 
responsive to return to relax state than the other two test environment. The subjects were all the university students where the medium of instruction was English so the learners’ brains are more comfortable with English than Bengali or Mathematics. Fig. 6 shows the brain relaxation curve over 
time which shows that Brain takes less time to be relaxed for 
English test and more time for Mathematics test. 
C. Mathematical Modeling: 
Mathematical modeling of brain relaxation is performed 
with least square method. Figs.7 (a)-(c) shows the brain 
relaxation modeling with mathematical formulation. 
Equations (6)-(8) shows the brain relaxation modeled 
expression for Bengali, English and Mathematics test respectively. The normal of the residuals have also been calculated to find the best mathematical model. English has the least norm of the residuals 0.088 indicating that the developed mathematical model is well suited with the 
original 	⁄ߙߚ Ratio of brain after English test whereas least 
suited for 	⁄ߙߚ Ratio after Mathematics test. In the case of 
math reading and math solving the value of the norm of the 
residual is 0.29392.   
