IV. CONCLUSION  
Learning of the learners depends on their cognitive 
capability which affects negatively due to stress. Stress of 
human brain is the unexpected brain condition which hampers brain response or human behavior. In this paper, stress is identified from the EEG band activation and beta to alpha ratio. The larger PSD value of beta band than alpha indicates the state of stress during different test environment. The beta to alpha band power ratio for relax state of the brain determine that alpha band is more activated for relaxation 
which maintains an inverse relationship due to stress. After 
performing the test, the beta and alpha band activation is observed over time from the beta to alpha ratio. Brain relaxation is obtained after 2.5 hours approximately after performing the test. Finally brain relaxation is modeled with mathematical formulation and quadratic mathematical expression is obtained for the brain relaxation modeling after test. The normal of the residuals shows the deviation of our proposed model. So, this work shows an innovative approach of mental stress and brain relaxation modeling for sustained mental task environment. 
