The SGATCNs model applies two SGAT layers. The ﬁrst SGAT layer receives the 
adjacency matrix of the discrete graph signals and the original node feature matrix to up-date its own node features against the aggreg ated neighboring node features of each node. 
The second SGAT layer receives the node feat ures that contain information about each 
node’s own features and its ﬁrst-order neighbors, and uses this as the basis for a further 
step of aggregation of node information. 
 
