A brain network was constructed based on the PLV connection matrix at a sparsity of
0.3 for subject-dependent cross-task cognitive workload-based experiments, and Figure 9
shows the results of task-independent cognitive workload recognition for 15 subjects under
seven classifiers. The proposed model achieved the highest classification accuracy for each
subject’s data, indicating that the model has high generalizability and high applicability
of performance for different subjects. For all subject, the task-independent classification
accuracies exceeded 60%, with six subjects having accuracies of over 65% and three subjects
